NAME

hci_blockage - the ORPG Blockage display tool

SYNOPSIS

hci_blockage

DESCRIPTION

This HCI task displays the blockage data graphically. The blockage data
exists in radial format with an azimuth interval of 0.1 degree and range
interval of 1 kilometer out to 230 kilometers.  

The data display range is automatically adjusted to the min/max values
found in the file.  The user has the option to change the display range by
selecting the "Display Range" button and adjusting the values in the Data
Range window.  Blockage data are displayed in the range 0 to 100% by default.
This range can also be adjusted in the Data Range window.

Blockage data exist at all levels starting at -1.0 degree elevation up to the
first level where no blockage is detected, in 0.1 degree intervals.  A combo
box widget is defined containing all levels.  It the Blockage type is selected,
then any one of these levels can be selected from the Blockage Level menu.

A vertical profile of the data along any selected radial is displayed in the
area below the menu buttons.  A new radial can be selected in "Raw" mode by
selecting a location on the blockage display.  A blinking line is displayed
along the selected radial.

